== Pudding ==

> The chocolate pots will take 2-3 hours to set so we'd recommend getting them prepared earlier in the day. However, they'll still be delicious if you only leave them in the fridge for a few minutes. Either way, make your pudding (all 3 steps) before you start cooking your main.

Remove the @cream cheese{100%grams} from the fridge so that it reaches room temperature.

Heat 2cm @water{2%cm} in a #small saucepan{} on medium heat until just simmering.

Pop the @chocolate chips{50%grams} into a #heatproof bowl{} and sit it snugly on top of the small saucepan. Stir the chocolate until melted, then remove from the heat and allow it to cool, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine the cream cheese, @salted caramel sauce{40%grams}, @sugar{2%tsp} and @creme fraiche{75%grams} (keep the rest for the main).

Fold in the cooled melted chocolate, then mix until well combined.

Pour the mixture into appropriately sized #glasses/ramekins{}. Cover with cling film and pop into the fridge to set - they'll take ~{2-3%hours} to fully set, but will still be delicious if you want to eat them straight away.

Enjoy!

== Main ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}(skin removed) onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Spread the @fresh pesto{32%grams} over the top of each fillet, then top with the @breadcrumbs{10%grams}, pressing it on lightly to cover the pesto. Drizzle the salmon with a little @oil{}.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the crumb is golden and the fish is cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{225%grams}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the prawns, green beans and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Stir the @water{100%milliliters} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and two thirds of the @creme fraiche{225%grams} into the prawns.

Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the lemon zest, half the lemon juice (or as much as you'd like), @butter{20%grams} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams} into the creamy sauce. Stir to combine.

Stir the tagliatelle into the sauce until well coated.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, and a squeeze of lemon juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the tagliatelle and sauce between #bowls{}.

Top each bowl with a pesto crusted salmon fillet. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!